    <p>
      Now approximate <m>\lim_{x\to 0} \sin(x)/x</m> numerically.
      We already approximated the value of this limit as 1 graphically in <xref ref="fig_sinx_over_x">Figure</xref>.
      The table in <xref ref="table_sinx_2">Figure</xref>
      shows the value of <m>\sin(x)/x</m> for values of <m>x</m> near 0.
      Ten places after the decimal point are shown to highlight how close to 1 the value of
      <m>\sin(x)/x</m> gets as <m>x</m> takes on values very near 0.
      We include the <m>x=0</m> row in bold again to stress that we are not concerned with the value of our function at <m>x=0</m>,
      only on the behavior of the function <em>near</em> 0.
    </p>

